public abstract class AbstractDynInterval<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements DynInterval<T>

AbstractDynInterval is the abstract class which provides generic methods to set and get dynamic value intervals. It represent a value list and its right half-open interval. Intervals are convenient for representing events that each occupy a continuous period of time. A half-open interval is an ordered pair of real numbers [startTime, endTime[ with startTime =< endTime, where startTime is included and endTime is excluded.

Author:
Sabina Sara Pfister
